Description: PLEASE NOTE: This listing is only for the U.S. Lower 48 states. I am the original owner of this guitar. It has seen little use and is in excellent condition. Neck is straight; no buzz; frets have a lifetime left. Three-way switch and controls (including the push-pull tone control which taps the humbuckers for single coil sounds) all work as they should. It does have some aesthetic flaws which I've captured in the last two pictures. A couple of tiny dings and three I-don't-know-what along the bottom. Not exactly what I'd call chips; don't really look like scratches to me, but there they are. Could be finish flaws I never noticed until I was actually looking for them. If something I haven't specifically pointed out as being a flaw catches your eye then it most likely is a reflection or dust. If it bugs you and you want a few additional photos for peace of mind just let me know. Of course you have the very superficial scratch here and there that is difficult to see and even harder to capture in photos. Comes with the original PRS gig bag and tremolo arm. Insured shipping via UPS Ground to U.S. Lower 48 only. Thanks and good luck!
